# ~/.tmux-help

TMUX KEYMAP
===========

Leader: Ctrl+s

HELP
  F1             show this help (q to close)

SPLITS (vim commands)
  C-s :sp        horizontal split
  C-s :vs        vertical split
  C-s :q         close pane
  C-s :qa        close window
  C-s :w         detach

PANE NAVIGATION
  C-s h          move left
  C-s j          move down
  C-s k          move up
  C-s l          move right
  C-s w          cycle panes

PANE RESIZE
  C-s H          resize left
  C-s J          resize down
  C-s K          resize up
  C-s L          resize right

WINDOWS
  C-s ,          new window
  C-s Ctrl+k     previous window
  C-s Ctrl+j     next window
  C-s Tab        last window

SESSIONS & WINDOWS
  F2             tree view (x=kill)
  C-s :new -s X  new session named X
  C-s $          rename session

SESSION PERSISTENCE (survives restart)
  C-s Ctrl+s     save session
  C-s Ctrl+r     restore session
               (auto-saves every 5min, auto-restores on start)

OTHER
  C-s z          zoom pane (toggle)
  C-s r          reload config
  C-s Escape     copy mode (v=select, y=yank, p=paste)
